Package com.kaleshwarsingh.addressbookmanager

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Address
    Provides a convenient way of representing an address, regardless of the format."
    AddressBook
    Resizable-array implementation of an address book.
    AddressBookManager
    This class allows you to create and manage multiple address books.
    AddressBookManagerMenu
    Displays the options available to the user for an AddressBookManager and takes input from the user which specifies the desired option.
    AddressBookMenu
    Displays the options available to the user for an AddressBook and takes input from the user which specifies the desired option.
    AddressMenu
    Display the options available to the user for an Address and takes input from the user, which specifies the desired option.
    EntryMenu
    Displays the options available to the user for a Person (entry) and takes input from the user, which specifies the desired option.
    Main
    Driver class for the address book manager application.
    Person
    Provides a convenient way of representing a Person with first and last names, address and phone number.
    PhoneNumber
    Provides convenient way of representing a standard 10-digit phone number, regardless of the way the phone number is entered.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidAddressException
    Thrown by an Address to indicate that the address received does not match the pattern for the expected type.
    InvalidNameException
    Thrown by a Person if the first name received is empty.
    InvalidPhoneNumberException
    Thrown by a PhoneNumber to indicate that the phone number received does not match the pattern of a valid phone number.
